==Footnotes==
*{{note label|Note1|a|a}}For lists of all American League pennant winners see [[American League pennant winners 1901-68]], and [[American League Championship Series]]
*{{note label|Note2|b|b}}The World Series was canceled after the [[San Francisco Giants|New York Giants]] refused to play.
*{{note label|Note3|c|c}}The season was partially canceled due to a player's strike that closed the MLB for 50 days.
*{{note label|Note4|d|d}}The season was partially canceled due to a player's strike that closed the MLB for 223 days.
*{{note label|Note5|e|e}}The Red Sox finished 95-67 and with the same record as the New York Yankees, but although the Yankees had won more previous games, they won the American League East and the Red Sox had to settle for the American League Wild Card.

